  "sub_category": "Zone",
  "description": "A defensive strategy where each player is assigned to guard a specific area (zone) of the court rather than a specific offensive player. The entire defensive formation shifts seamlessly in response to ball movement. It is highly effective at protecting the paint, stopping penetration, and forcing opponents into low-percentage outside shots, though it can be vulnerable to quick ball reversals and elite three-point shooting.",
